title: For Sale:  Amazing SKS BULLPUP rifle with mags.  Ready to go! $525 WOW!!
location: North Port, South West Florida, Florida
postcontent:
Trade offers are encouraged via text or email.
text REDACTED
email REDACTED

This weapon needs nothing.  It is tight and complete and shoots perfectly.  The stock alone cost$350 plus the Norinco SKS.  I also added the cantilever scope mount/shell deflector (to keep the sheels from hitting the scope).  It is loads of fun - I am just looking for something new to buy or trade for - I get bored of guns periodically.  This is a much more fun rifle than a standard sks in the bullpup stock.  It changes the center of gravity of the rifle and makes it SO much more manuverable.  You will love it the very first time you shoot it.  It comes with (2) 20 round polymer magazines.  These magazines work the best with the SG Systems bullpup stock.

This is loads of fun and the (pictured) extended magazine release is unique to the SG Sytems bullpup stock.

Are you asking why a bullpup sks would have a scope? Don't.  The scope has the illuminated retical to help locate targets quickly in low light.  The beauty of the bullpup rifle is that it's compact and retains the full length barrel so it is accurate at long range.

With the scope zeroed I was able to hit 12" reactive targets up to 150 yards.  I am sure its accurate to much farther than I can shoot.

The bullpup conversion makes this a really practical tactical weapon that you can move and shoot with in confined spaces.  

I love the SKS - right now I dont need this rifle.  I have to say that having recently fired an AK47 after owning this sks for some time - the sks is more fun to shoot.  The AK kicks more with the same ammunition.  The sks is more stable - the AK wants to jump all over the place.  I have fired neither at full auto and I believe I would rather have a full auto sks than the AK as well.

My son prefered to use a REDDOT optic on this because it let him engage targets quicker and my older eyes need the magnification.

Priced to move -- $525 is a firm price - no cash offers below $525

title: Want To Buy:  .
For Sale/Trade:  Colt Magnum Carry, Stainless, 357 Magnum, Magna Port Custom.
postcontent: Manufactured in 1999 only, this was colt’s last double action revolver and is a very collectible variation. It has a “beefed up” top strap to increase the strength of the frame so that it can handle the more powerful .357 magnum cartridge. This rare stainless steel small revolver has been sent to Magna Port for porting and full on custom action job. Magna Port does not stamp every gun they port only full custom guns. This is a once in a life time gun. It shows no wear other than as small drag line between the cylinder stops. It is complete with its original case. This is one of Colt’s more scarce revolvers with a very short production run. Magna Port was and still is the best and will make this gun more manageable firing hot .357 magnum loads. This is a very cool gun and would make a great addition to any Colt collection.

There are pictures stolen off of armslist to be used for fake ads stealing from innocent, hard working Americans.  I had someone personally try to sell me my own gun.
To the consumer, be smart.  DO NOT mail money orders.  Do not give out your personal information is something seems strange.  DO FTF transactions or, require  seller to use another dealer to handle the purchase and money.
To the criminals, YOU are now being watched.  You can create alias emails and phone numbers all you want.  Your IP address doesn't lie.  And we have created a system that "pings" certain IP address or e-mails as soon as they are used in Armslist.  Continue to do criminal acts on this site and I assure you, you will get caught.  Your information will also be released to the individuals you impacted.  The victims can take this and prosecute to the fullest extent.  Remember, who is number 1 on the list of steeling ID's and illegal gun purchases???  TERRORISTS! And we have caught on to you.
